h4 #{Constants[Enums.Positions.GUARD]} or #{Constants[Enums.Positions.JACK]} only
p
    | A #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} is a type of 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.SLAM}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.SLAM]} 
    | that ocurrs when the target player is on the ground.
    | The player making the #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} attempt may not 
    | move as part of this action unless they have the 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Abilities.DOES_THIS_HURT}") #{Constants[Enums.Abilities.DOES_THIS_HURT]} 
    | ability.
    | The only response the target of a #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} attempt 
    | can make is 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.DODGE}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DODGE]}
    | , which they do at -1 die (for being on the floor).

h5 #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} is a 3 dice Strength test (1)
ul
    li +1 if the player is a #{Constants[Enums.Positions.GUARD]}.
    li -1 per opposing player threatening the hex the player is in (maximum of -2).

table.table.table-striped
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} succeeds.
        td Nothing happens.
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} doubles
        td
            | The target must make an 
            a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.ARMOR_CHECK}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.ARMOR_CHECK]} 
            | against the difference in the number of successes between both players'
            | rolls (e.g. If the winning roll was 3 and the target's roll was 1, then 
            | target player makes a 2 dice #{Constants[Enums.Actions.ARMOR_CHECK]}).

p
    | Note that #{Constants[Enums.Actions.STOMP]} is a Foul, and the opposing player 
    | may make a 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.REF_CHECK}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.REF_CHECK]} 
    | after the action has been resolved.
